      "span_text": "The voltage-independent NMDA channel (NMDA VI ) is based loosely on the type of channel found between excitatory cells in layer 4 of visual cortex; we used τ r = 150 ms for this simulated receptor as well. s(t) is the synaptic weight at time t. x is the short-term depression/potentiation scaling factor as above; gain NMDA is the ratio of NMDA to AMPA conductance and is found experimentally to be less than one (Myme et al., 2003)."
